  ${
    $d k j n $.
    $( The sum of the reciprocals of the triangle numbers converge to two.
       (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 23-Apr-2014.)  (Revised by Mario Carneiro,
       22-May-2014.) $)
    trirecip $p |- sum_ k e. NN ( 2 / ( k x. ( k + 1 ) ) ) = 2 $=
      ( vn cn c2 cv c1 caddc co cmul cdiv csu wcel cc wceq 2cn a1i syl wtru cli
      nnuz cc0 peano2nn nnmulcl mpdan nncn nnne0 divrec syl3anc sumeq2i cmpt cz
      wne 1z cfv id opreq1 opreq12d opreq2d oprex fvmpt adantl wa wi cr nnrecre
      eqid recnd idi wbr cdm trireciplem seqex breldm isummulc2 isumclim eqtr3d
      cseq trud mulid1i 3eqtri ) CDAEZWAFGHZIHZJHZAKCDFWCJHZIHZAKZDFIHZDCWDWFAW
